Analyzing various traditional singing styles, developing personal singing style based on imitating archive recordings and authentic singing situations, applying the experience as a lead singer in performing framework. Participating in various contemporary events and festivals, which focus on traditional singing. Comprehensive study of traditional song repertoire (singers, traditions, styles etc) in a certain region (parish).Objectives/eesmärkid:  Developing knowledge of traditional singing styles and providing practical instructions on how to create and develop personal singing style based on traditional singing techiques. Participating in various contemporary performace settings in traditional events.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing the course, the student will - understand and interpret folk song lyrics; - acquire knowledge of and apply fluently stylistic features characteristic of traditional singing styles; - acquire skills required for assaying various contemporary singing situations and be able to participate in them.
